  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Integrated intervention to  improve livelihoods and increase protection of conflict affected persons</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">-Improved food security and nutrition among conflict affected HH
-Reduced malnutrition amongst Under5 children, pregnant and lactating mothers.
-Improved awareness on GBV and reduced incidences of GBV among the targeted communities</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1.Distribute cash, fishing gears, seeds and tools
2.Training of 108 fish flocks in simple fish preservation techniques. 
3.Training of Nine (9) producer groups (15 members each) on the management of vegetable gardens.
4.Conduct MUAC screening and referral of children, pregnant mothers and lactating mothers.
5. Conduct awareness to mothers and caregivers on the hygienic handling of food
6. Refer vulnerable children to the child friendly spaces for acute malnutrition response.
7.Training on changing attitudes towards culturally ingrained violence against women and GBV cause trauma.
8. Post distribution monitoring and evaluation.</narrative>
  </description>
